.TH "hsi_get_channel_id_by_name" 9 "hsi_get_channel_id_by_name" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hsi_get_channel_id_by_name \- acquire channel id by channel name
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" hsi_get_channel_id_by_name
.BI "(struct hsi_client *cl "  ","
.BI "char *name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cl" 12
HSI client, which uses the channel
.IP "name" 12
name the channel is known under
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Clients can call this function to get the hsi channel ids similar to
requesting IRQs or GPIOs by name. This function assumes the same
channel configuration is used for RX and TX.

Returns -errno on error or channel id on success.
